    "The PCC quantifies the linear correlation between two variables and is a value between -1 and 1, where the higher value indicates a higher correlation.",
    "On 50 randomly selected unsafe samples, three human annotators (information in Appendix C) scored model analysis according to the same criteria that prompt the GPT-4 scorer.",
    "The average PCC on Effectiveness is 0.91, indicating the reliability of pairwise evaluation for the risk identification test.",
    "The full results across models are listed in Table 7 in Appendix D.3.",
    "Notably, for GPT-4 answers, the PCC between the automatic scorer and human is 0.89, showing little bias."
